M|rules|title: useEffectEvent for Stable Callback Refs
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: prevents effect re-runs
M|rules|tags: advanced, hooks, useEffectEvent, refs, optimization
M|rules|Access latest values in callbacks without adding them to dependency arrays. Prevents effect re-runs while avoiding stale closures.
M|rules|**Incorrect (effect re-runs on every callback change):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function SearchInput({ onSearch }: { onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|const timeout = setTimeout(() => onSearch(query), 300)
M|rules|return () => clearTimeout(timeout)
M|rules|}, [query, onSearch])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (using React's useEffectEvent):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { useEffectEvent } from 'react';
M|rules|function SearchInput({ onSearch }: { onSearch: (q: string) => void }) {
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|const onSearchEvent = useEffectEvent(onSearch)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|const timeout = setTimeout(() => onSearchEvent(query), 300)
M|rules|return () => clearTimeout(timeout)
M|rules|}, [query])
M|rules|}
M|rules|```